\b0 \cf0  
\fs20 7:35:11 pm
\fs26 \
\pard\pardeftab720

\b \cf0 Yeah. These all touch on the main idea. The problem is that there could be conflicts in what gets inherited. Suppose Game and Product both have a toString method. Which one would BoardGame have? The first one defined? Both of them? And how would you refer to them? super only gets you to one superclass.
